      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:1:3:9",
      "text": [
        " قَالَ لِي أَبُو عَبْدِ اللَّهِ ( عليه السلام ) بَلَغَنِي أَنَّهُ وُلِدَ لَكَ ابْنَةٌ فَتُسْخِطُهَا وَ مَا عَلَيْكَ مِنْهَا رَيْحَانَةٌ تَشَمُّهَا وَ قَدْ كُفِيتَ رِزْقَهَا وَ قَدْ كَانَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ( صلى الله عليه وآله ) أَبَا بَنَاتٍ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ahmad Bin Muhammad Al Aasimy, from Ali Bin Al Hassan Al Tumayli, from Ali Bin Asbaat, from his father, form Al Jaroud Bin Al Munzar who said, ",
          "‘Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> said to me: ‘It has reached me that a daughter has been born unto you, so it angered you, and what is upon you from her is an aroma for you to smell, and her sustenance has been Sufficed with; and Rasool-Allah<sup>saww</sup> was a father of daughters’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "9. Ahmad ibn Muhammad al-‘Asemiy has narrated from Ali ibn al-Hassan al-Taymuliy from Ali ibn Asbat from his father from al-Jarud ibn al-Mundhir who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, once said to me, ‘I am told a girl is born to you whom you dislike. What has she brought upon you? She is a sweet smelling flower you enjoy and her sustenance is guaranteed, besides, the Messenger of Allah was a father of girls.’” "
        ]
      }
    },
